<br>
Is it honorable?  Probably not, but I dual to win.  And an enchanter has to be creative.  Challenge me only at risk to your xp bar, and I expect the same.  It isn't something to be taken lightly.<br>
<br>
Valquiss Silverpalm<br>
<br>
P.S. Notable exceptions would be organized touraments, duals between friends, etc. when a degree of courtesy is expected.  But a challenge out of the blue...you have to expect some risk. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubladeofevil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Blade of Evil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/4/02 12:38:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=200.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://thevornskr.homestead.com/files/velveportrait.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: My third rant....at VI</span><hr size=1> I hear ya Ichi.  All I can suggest is save mana for one last tap.  When their life is at a point where you can't see red (or just barely) try to tap them.  I guarantee they won't lose exp if you kill with a tap.<br>
<br>
If they are that low, dotted, and keep fighting and interupt your attempts to tap them, it's their own fault.<br>
<br>
Or if worst comes to worst, and you don't have mana, but do have the Touch up, HT them.  I know you won't lose exp this way either, but its up to you to decide whether or not the person is worth your HT. <p><B><font color="darkred">Velve D'Verin</font><Br>
