<br>
In my experience dueling as an enchanter, I found that there was MUCH more fun to be had in not winning the fight, ironically enough. I was never comfortable with the idea of experience loss even with people I was roleplaying good/evil with.  Getting creative, I discovered the abject humiliation that charm can provide.  After a time, nobody wanted to duel my enchanter for the sheer reason that I would keep them as pets forever, make them stand up, sit down, run up to people and report that I was their master, send them at orc pawns or other trivial mobs, and as soon as it broke, stun/mez/charm (or Gravity Flux if I really wanted to freak them out) and begin the process anew.  When I figured they had enough, I would usually send a tell with &quot;Next time, I will not let you off this easily - we shall see how you fare against a Kromrif Guard&quot;.  Believe me, even though the message went out that they won the duel, they certainly never felt like winners <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
There are other very fun ways to discourage opponents in a duel without outright killing them.  For instance, Debuffs + ill prepared melees with heavy armor = totally immobile and stupid feeling opponent.  Mana drain can have the same effect on casters who are not prepared.<br>
<br>
In addition to the Harm Touch idea of Velve's, if the recycle time is an issue and you are dueling a friend, just have them kill you next - instant recycle of Harm Touch. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/unimiane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nimiane</A> at: 1/4/02 9:50:29 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/upakuachuan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PakuaChuan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/4/02 10:15:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=200.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: My third rant....at VI</span><hr size=1> &quot;Getting creative, I discovered the abject humiliation that charm can provide. After a time, nobody wanted to duel my enchanter for the sheer reason that I would keep them as pets forever, make them stand up, sit down, run up to people and report that I was their master, send them at orc pawns or other trivial mobs, and as soon as it broke, stun/mez/charm (or Gravity Flux if I really wanted to freak them out) and begin the process anew.&quot;<br>
