Valquiss, I can totally understand being irritated with the duel request like that.  I hardly ever accept duel requests from people I don't know unless they are really, really, really asking for it (as in being exceptionally rude).  I generally only duel friends, because it's easier to stick with the &quot;No DoT, no falling damage, no NPCs&quot; type rules, just as you mentioned.  I think for me it was all about getting friends bunched together in an arena to blast them with Gravity Flux more than anything else.  There is nothing funnier than watching half your guild fly a zillion feet into the air, come crunching down, and beg for another <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
